Sixty-four (64) diarrheic samples were received from foals less than 3 months of age and 1 sample was obtained from a foal that was 112 days old at the day of sampling. Thirty-two (32) samples were received from Belgium, 1 from France, 17 from Germany, 3 from Hungary, 2 from Italy, 5 from Slovenia, 4 from Sweden and 1 from The Netherlands (Table 1
). From each location (stud farm or private owner) a maximum of 3 samples was collected, with the exception of 1 stud farm in Germany from which 5 samples were received. The breed, gender, date of birth of and clinical signs observed in the foals are reported in Supplementary Data 1, and Table 2
.
